            <h1 class="gowun-batang-bold">	Aam Aadmi Bima Yojana  :</h1>
            <div id="infowrap-1">   
                <div id="infobox1">
                    <ul>
                        <li><p> Aam Aadmi Bima Yojana (AABY) is a government-sponsored social security scheme that aims to provide affordable life insurance coverage to the unorganized sector of the population in India. The scheme was launched in 2007 and is administered by the Life Insurance Corporation of India (LIC).</p></li>
                        <li><p>The primary objective of the scheme is to provide financial support to the economically weaker sections of the society in case of the death or disability of the earning member of the family. The scheme targets those who work in unorganized sectors such as agriculture, fishery, dairy, handloom, construction, and other similar occupations.</p></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="infobox2">
                    <ul>
                        <li><p> Financial assistance: The AABY scheme provides financial assistance to the family members of the insured in case of the insured person's death or disability.</p></li>
                        <li><p>Affordable premiums: The premiums for the AABY scheme are very affordable and are subsidized by the government, making it accessible to people from all economic backgrounds.</p></li>
                        <li><p>Coverage for natural calamities: The AABY scheme also covers natural calamities such as floods, earthquakes, etc..</p></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div id="infowrap-2">
                <div id="infobox3">
                    <ul>
                        <li><p>Easy enrollment: The enrollment process for the AABY scheme is simple and easy, and individuals can enroll at any time of the year..</p></li>
                        <li><p>Coverage for women: The AABY scheme also provides special benefits for women, including maternity benefits and coverage for female-headed households</p></li>
                        
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="infobox4">
                    <h2>Eligibility to apply for for Aam Aadmi Bima Yojna :</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li><p>Age Limit: The scheme is open to individuals between the ages of 18 and 59 years.</p></li>
                        <li><p>. Income Limit: The applicant should belong to a household below the poverty line, with an annual income not exceeding Rs. 1,00,000.</p></li>
                        <li><p>Social Security Scheme: The applicant should not be covered under any other social security scheme, such as the National Pension Scheme, Employee's State Insurance Scheme, or any other government-run life insurance scheme.</p></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
